caption: It is truly breathtaking how often every one of the baristas here manage to put foam in an order that specifically asks for none - almost every day M-F. But they all do it with a cool “I know what I’m doing” attitude, so maybe it’s me? Are my preferences wrong? Maybe they know something I don’t know. My Caffe Misto order with no foam STAYS though (and unfortunately so will the foam).

Went to this Starbucks to get my first Pumpkin Cream Cold Brew of the season. Been waiting all year for them to come back! Not only did we wait 15+ minutes for our drinks, but it was made completely wrong (just looked like a caramel colored iced coffee, and didn’t even taste like pumpkin, and the woman (who I believe was the manager) was condescending and rude. When I said this isn’t a pumpkin cream cold brew, she said “yes it is, is that your name? That’s what you ordered”.... ok lady, does this look anything like the photo? NO. Don’t waste your time or money going to this unorganized, sad excuse for a Starbucks.

A "large" in city Starbucks, more along the size of a suburban location with patio and light retail section. Fairly quick service with the usual morning surge, a little less crowded than some locations in the city that are directly on a mass transit artery.  On an odd note has a combination of European tavern shared table seating, Cafe tables, single stuffed chairs, counter seating, and the patio table seating. Sounds like you can seat a army division, however there is just an odd variety of seating rather than an above average amount for the size of the location.
